    <p>Everything you need to know about the upcoming climax of the Demon Slayer anime</p>
  </header>

  <main>
    <article>
      <section class="intro">
        <h2>The Wait Is Over</h2>
        <p>After months of speculation, the official trailer for the *Infinity Castle Arc* has finally dropped, and fans are losing their minds. The trailer delivers stunning visuals, haunting music, and a glimpse at some of the most intense battles we’ll see in the entire *Demon Slayer* series.</p>
        <p>In this article, we’ll break down every moment, explain what it means for the story, and explore what to expect from the final battle between the Hashira and Muzan Kibutsuji’s inner circle.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What Is the Infinity Castle?</h2>
        <p>The Infinity Castle is Muzan’s dimension — a shifting, eerie fortress created and controlled by Nakime, the Biwa-playing demon. It’s a vast and chaotic labyrinth where time and space distort, making it the perfect battleground for the most dangerous demons and Demon Slayers alike.</p>
        <p>The trailer opens with an ominous view of the castle: moving walls, infinite staircases, and ghostly lights. This setting symbolizes the endgame. The stakes are higher than ever.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Who Appears in the Trailer?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Tanjiro Kamado:</strong> Determined and scarred from previous battles, we see him entering the castle ready to confront Muzan directly.</li>
          <li><strong>Nezuko Kamado:</strong> Still partially demon, Nezuko’s fate remains a central mystery — will she regain full humanity or play a crucial role in battle?</li>
          <li><strong>Hashira Squad:</strong> Giyu, Sanemi, Mitsuri, Obanai, Gyomei, and more all appear preparing for battle. Their presence confirms this arc will focus heavily on their final moments.</li>
          <li><strong>Upper Moons:</strong> Kokushibo, Akaza, Doma, and Nakime are shown — each poised for their final confrontations.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Major Battles Teased</h2>
        <p>The trailer teases multiple fight scenes, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Sanemi & Gyomei vs Kokushibo</strong> – A fast-paced clash with the Upper Rank One demon, featuring moon breathing and raw brute force.</li>
          <li><strong>Mitsuri & Obanai vs Nakime</strong> – A spatial battle inside the shifting castle halls.</li>
          <li><strong>Tanjiro & Giyu vs Akaza</strong> – A rematch with personal stakes and emotional flashbacks.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each fight is animated with extraordinary quality — breathing techniques and blood demon arts sparkle with detail.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>The Final Showdown with Muzan</h2>
        <p>One of the most chilling scenes in the trailer shows Muzan's eyes glowing red as he declares, “All demons exist to serve me.” He’s shown briefly facing Tanjiro, and fans are speculating this will lead into the climactic sunrise battle — the most emotional and devastating part of the series.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Animation Quality</h2>
        <p>Studio Ufotable has outdone itself again. From the lighting in the Infinity Castle to the fluidity of sword techniques, everything looks polished. The trailer showcases detailed facial expressions, weather effects, and cinematic camera angles, raising expectations sky-high.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Release Date & Episode Format</h2>
        <p>According to the end card of the trailer, the Infinity Castle arc will begin airing in **Fall 2025**, likely as a multi-part season or even split films. Fans expect 3 major arcs: Infinity Castle, Final Battle, and Epilogue.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What Fans Are Saying</h2>
        <p>Twitter, Reddit, and YouTube exploded within minutes of the trailer dropping. Hashtags like #InfinityCastle and #DemonSlayerFinalArc trended worldwide. Most fans agree: this will be the most emotional arc yet, with multiple beloved characters facing their end.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>The Infinity Castle trailer isn’t just a teaser — it’s a warning. A signal that *Demon Slayer* is ready to break hearts, blow minds, and leave its legacy as one of the greatest anime stories ever told.</p>
        <p>So get your tissues, your theories, and your breathing techniques ready — 2025 is going to be unforgettable.</p>
      </section>
